
[1]methodical

   METHOD'ICAL, a. Arranged in convenient order; disposed in a just and
   natural manner, or in a manner to illustrate a subject, or to
   facilitate practical operations; as a methodical arrangement of the
   parts of a discourse or of arguments; a methodical treatise; methodical
   accounts.
